The paper focuses on developing an automated cell type classification pipeline using convolutional neural networks for lung cancer pathology images. This involves image analysis, feature extraction, and prognostic modeling. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves deep learning techniques, which could also place it in the cs.DL (Deep Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques for feature extraction, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
